- VSCode Version: 1.1.0-alpha
- OS Version: Windows10

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Create an empty project with  dotnet new :
    >mkdir MyApplication
    >cd MyApplication
    >dotnet new
    >dotnet restore
2. Follow instruction for project setup from https://github.com/OmniSharp/omnisharp-vscode/blob/master/debugger.md
3. Launch app and open project folder.
4. Add below code to make app multi-threaded.
public static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            Thread t1 = new Thread(WriteY1);
            t1.Name = "First Thread";
            Thread t2 = new Thread(WriteY2);
            // Kick off a new thread
            t1.Start();  // running WriteY1()
            t2.Start();  // running WriteY2()
            // Simultaneously, do something on the main thread.  
            for (int i = 0; i < 1000; i++)
                Console.Write("3");
        }
        static void WriteY1()
        {
            for (int p = 0; p < 1000; p++) Console.Write("1");
        }
        static void WriteY2()
        {
            for (int q = 0; q < 1000; q++) Console.Write("2");
        }
   }
5. Add break point in main thread and build app. 
6. start debugging and verify app behavior.
7. Add variables (i, p and q) in watch window and perform debugging bit faster with F10 to verify changes in the variable's value in watch window.

